# Finding 055
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Duplicate CLI entrypoint wrappers
- File + line(s): `packages/tooling/jskit/bin/jskit.js:1-8`, `packages/tooling/create-app/bin/jskit-create-app.js:1-8`
- Why it can drift/fail: Two identical CLI entrypoints wrap `runCli` the same way. Any change to startup behavior (e.g., error handling or tracing) must be updated twice.
- Concrete impact: Drift between CLI packages and inconsistent exit behavior if only one wrapper changes.
- Exact remediation: Extract a shared CLI entrypoint helper or symlink/alias a single wrapper script.

## Resolution
- Summary: introduced `@jskit-ai/cli-entrypoint` to host the shared wrapper and updated both CLI bins to use it.
- Tests:
  - npm -ws --if-present test (failed: missing workspace deps like jskit-app-scripts/vitest and multiple ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND; jskit tests fail without @jskit-ai/cli-entrypoint in node_modules)
